<br>
Does it REALLY make more aggro?  Oh, I know I get summoned and pull aggro a hell of a lot more with SoS than I ever did back when I used draughts... but is it really more aggro or just the increase in DPS?<br>
<br>
Using un-hasted, un-focused, un-mana preserved, non-instaclicked numbers...<br>
<br>
3 draughts is 2850 damage in (3 + 2.25 + 3 + 2.25 + 3) 13.5 seconds.<br>
1 SoS is 2740 damage in 8 seconds.<br>
<br>
That's a full 5.5 second difference, and in battle, 5.5 seconds is a long time.<br>
<br>
I think a good experiment to do would be to group with a warrior and cleric, and just chain Draughts until you get summoned.  Then fight the same mob but wait 5.5 seconds, cast SoS, wait 2.25 + 5.5 seconds then cast SoS again.  And if Chaining 6 Draughts without concussion doesn't get you summoned while using the delayed Strikes of Solusek does, then yes it's more aggro.<br>
<br>
It's the same argument with Rains.  Remember, rains are 12 seconds long from cast to last wave.  Obviously though you can concussion while the waves are hitting so it's easier to control aggro.<br>
<br>
I know using Strike of Solusek gets me aggro more than any other spell I have ever used, but it's also the fastest damage (highest DPS) spell I have ever used... so couldn't it all be subjective? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13385">Sage Xarinthus Nihilflare, Nukanist of the 65th Degree Burns</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
